What is a Quant?

In his book, THE QUANTS, Scott Patterson really hit the nail on the head. He described Quants as those who searching for the truth - the truth being the universal underlying hidden dynamics in the markets. That has always captivated me.

•	build computational models of the world

•	apply the scientific method to finance

One thing that makes this field fascinating is that things are always changing:

•	new development in market

•	new datasets

•	new computational techniques

Signals in financial data are very faint. You need to combine scientific research with understanding of markets, intuition of markets, and domain knowledge about markets.

•	Isaac Newton who experienced significant stock trading losses in his personal account: I can predict the movements of the heavens, but I cannot predict the madness of people.
